ion proper in Bantu languages. Finkbeiner discusses a case of triplication in German, contrasting it with the framework of reduplication. Kallergi & Konstantinidou provide an detailed insight into several kinds of echo formations in Modern Greek, including diachronic aspects. Rozhanskiy's focus is on unexpected reduplicative patterns found in the formation of Komi ideophones. Stolz delivers a thorough crosslinguistic investigation on reduplicative phenomena, favouring the canonical approach over the prototype method.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 22. Mai 2018) 4aEcho Formation. 4aNon-Canonical Reduplication. 4aNon-Prototypical Reduplication. 4aReduplication.1 aUrdze, Aina, eeditor.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishz978311060425208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018z9783110603255oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2018 Englishz978311060407808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2018z9783110603170oZDB-23-DSP0 cEPUBz97831105971340 cprintz978311059700440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110599329423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110599329.jpg  a978-3-11-060407-8  EBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2018 Englishb2018  a978-3-11-060425-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishb2018  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG  aZDB-23-DGGb2017  aZDB-23-DSPb2018